    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "a0fa94b2_d8c0e865",
        "filename": "cq/api/config/v2/cq.proto",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 214,
      "author": {
        "id": 1002539
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-06-14T22:56:48Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I don\u0027t understand why this is needed... Why can\u0027t we launch the tryjobs as soon as all CLs in a set have the vote? What is the use case of tweaking this value?",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 214,
        "startChar": 27,
        "endLine": 214,
        "endChar": 46
      },
      "revId": "5099d240a89afa56bf59a5c09aba6d5b4fbdd20d",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "7fbe6b50_fa769c5c",
        "filename": "cq/api/config/v2/cq.proto",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 214,
      "author": {
        "id": 1141499
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-06-15T02:05:07Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "because reasons:\n1. suppose we adopt what you propose, and user forgets to vote on some CL. When would CQ stop waiting?\n2. maximal CL set depends on which CLs get votes. Even with trivial stack of 2 Cls {A1 \u003c- A2}: if user votes CQ+2 on A1 first, which can be tried on its own, CQ should still wait a bit to observe possible CQ+2 on A2.\nIt\u0027s gets more fun with complex cases like this:\n\n    A1 \u003c- A2 \u003c- A3\n           ^\n           |\n           v\n    B1  \u003c- B2 \u003c- B3\n\nhere if B3 gets CQ+2, clearly A1,A2,B1,B2 needs CQ+2, too (and in fact I wish future CQ with API would just infer that for the user and tell this in Gerrit UI) .\nbut ultimately this reduces to the first example: user may also wish A3 to be CQ-ed, too.",
      "parentUuid": "a0fa94b2_d8c0e865",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 214,
        "startChar": 27,
        "endLine": 214,
        "endChar": 46
      },
      "revId": "5099d240a89afa56bf59a5c09aba6d5b4fbdd20d",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "63430a3c_44996a83",
        "filename": "cq/api/config/v2/cq.proto",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 214,
      "author": {
        "id": 1002539
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-06-15T02:17:22Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "\u003e When would CQ stop waiting?\n\nI assumed it doesn\u0027t actually actively wait. When scanning Gerrit it assembles a graph of CLs. If all CLs in a component of this graph are approved, it launches an attempt. If not, it just ignores this component. \n\nSo if user forgets to vote on a CL, nothing at all will happen... I guess we can look at an yongest CQ+2/1 vote in a component and post a message \"You actually need to approve all other CLs too\" if it is older than X sec. Maybe stabilization_delay is doing exactly this?\n\nWith stabilization_delay\u003d30, does it mean the user have 30 sec to click all relevant buttons in Gerrit? What will happen if they don\u0027t do it fast enough?",
      "parentUuid": "7fbe6b50_fa769c5c",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 214,
        "startChar": 27,
        "endLine": 214,
        "endChar": 46
      },
      "revId": "5099d240a89afa56bf59a5c09aba6d5b4fbdd20d",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "9b610d2d_2b9d2b14",
        "filename": "cq/api/config/v2/cq.proto",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 214,
      "author": {
        "id": 1141499
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-06-15T02:33:11Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Yesish. CQ does effectively ignore CLs for at most `stabilization_delay` seconds (counted from the most recently voted CL in connected component). And then, if any CLs don\u0027t have votes but should, CQ posts a message about missing votes \u0026\u0026 removes existing votes. \nAdmittedly, the latter isn\u0027t perfect, it\u0027s just simplest to implement[1]\n\nAnd the above is what happens if you aren\u0027t fast enough. Effectively, they need to start from scratch.\n\n[1] and also I don\u0027t want to add more complexity into this with the current CQ codebase because:\n  * more complex interplay between legacy CQ and LUCI CQ during migration\n  * voting on CQ+1/2 labels isn\u0027t the optimal model even for 1 CL, let alone N CLs.",
      "parentUuid": "63430a3c_44996a83",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 214,
        "startChar": 27,
        "endLine": 214,
        "endChar": 46
      },
